Sleeping Dogs: Definitive Edition (played both DLCs too)

7 / 10 (good, I recommend it for players that like action/adventure games).

Scales: Excellent / Very good / Good / Mediocre / Bad.

The Positive:
* Good story;
* Good gameplay;
* Good graphics and art direction; 
* Good performance;
* Good main protagonist;
* Good voice acting;
* Good soundtrack and sound in effects and ambience;
* Good side activities like racing, fighting in arenas, cop’s job, events, people in need, etc;
* Good clothes customization, but preset clothing is always better because of passive stats;
* Good variety of vehicles;
* No artificially inserted DEI;
* The open world is small, but I felt like I was in Hong Kong.

The Neutral:
* Mediocre character customization for fighting and shooting;
* Mediocre NPCs in general;
* Mediocre camera behavior.

The Negative:
* Bad main story ending/climax. It’s very abrupt, uninteresting and uninspired.
